msgctxt "BloodyMoon00"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Whenever the clock strikes midnight on\n"
"unlucky nights, the sky turns blood red.\n"
"That's the <2.se_co>blood moon<3.re_co>.\n"
"When that happens, <4.se_co>monsters<5.re_co> come back\n"
"to life, no matter how many times you've\n"
"defeated them.\n"
"It's happened for so long now that no\n"
"one really pays it any mind, but I have no\n"
"plans to give up on my research."
msgstr ""

#. 1: set_colour (red)
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: sound
#. 4: text_size
#. 5: reset_colour
msgctxt "BloodyTalk00"
msgid ""
"<1.se_co><2.te_si><3.so>It's...so...RED!\n"
"So gloriously RED!<4.te_si><5.re_co>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: set_colour (red)
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: sound
#. 4: text_size
#. 5: reset_colour
msgctxt "BloodyTalk01"
msgid "<1.se_co><2.te_si><3.so>My blood...it's boiling!<4.te_si><5.re_co>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: set_colour (red)
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: sound
#. 4: text_size
#. 5: reset_colour
msgctxt "BloodyTalk02"
msgid "<1.se_co><2.te_si><3.so>Arise, monsters!<4.te_si><5.re_co>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: set_colour (red)
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: sound
#. 4: text_size
#. 5: reset_colour
msgctxt "BloodyTalk03"
msgid "<1.se_co><2.te_si><3.so>Gr...gr...gr...<4.te_si><5.re_co>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "FirstTalk00"
msgid "<1.so>Hmm..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound
msgctxt "FirstTalk01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Oh, sorry...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<2.so>I didn't notice you... I was a bit lost in\n"
"thought there."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "FirstTalk01_1"
msgid "<1.so>What's up?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: set_colour (red)
#. 2: reset_colour
#. 3: choice
msgctxt "FirstTalk02"
msgid ""
"I've been doing rigorous research day\n"
"and night to figure out the mystery of \n"
"that <1.se_co>blood moon<2.re_co>.<3.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound
msgctxt "FirstTalk03"
msgid ""
"<1.so>You don't know it?\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<2.so>That's inexcusable. Listen up and I'll tell\n"
"you about it."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: sound
msgctxt "FirstTalk04"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hmmm...<2.pa> Are you just pretending to\n"
"know what I was talking about?\n"
"\n"
"<3.so>That's fine, so long as you'll listen to me\n"
"now while I tell you about it."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "FirstTalk05"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hmm...<2.pa>\n"
"All the same, take a minute and listen\n"
"while I tell you about it."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "FirstTalk06"
msgid ""
"<1.so>For 100 years now, every so often when\n"
"the clock strikes midnight, the sky turns\n"
"red and a full moon rises...\n"
"At that moment, <2.se_co>monsters<3.re_co> that had been\n"
"previously defeated will come back\n"
"to life."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: set_colour (red)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: text_size
msgctxt "FirstTalk07"
msgid ""
"<1.so><2.te_si>And that's what is known as the\n"
"<3.se_co>blood moon<4.re_co>!<5.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (long)
#. 5: sound
#. 6: set_colour (red)
#. 7: reset_colour
msgctxt "FirstTalk08"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Why do the <2.se_co>monsters<3.re_co> return to life? <4.pa>\n"
"Why does it only happen when the sky\n"
"turns red?\n"
"No one really has the answers to those\n"
"questions. It's a mysterious\n"
"phenomenon...\n"
"<5.so>If you learn anything about the <6.se_co>blood\n"
"moon<7.re_co> as you travel, be sure to come\n"
"back and tell me."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound
#. 3: sound
msgctxt "GoodBye00"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hmm...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<2.so>Oh, I'm sorry...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<3.so>I spend so much time thinking about the\n"
"moon that it's all I can talk about."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "GoodBye01"
msgid "<1.so>Hmm..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "Moon00"
msgid "<1.so>Tonight is the <2.se_co>blood moon<3.re_co>, at last..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "Moon00_After"
msgid ""
"<1.so>The <2.se_co>blood moon <3.re_co>has come and gone.\n"
"Time to start waiting for the next one..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: pause (short)
msgctxt "Moon00_Befor"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I'm getting that feeling again...<2.pa>\n"
"Something is going to happen tonight.<3.pa>\n"
"I can taste it!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Moon00_Full"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Tonight is a full moon...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"Looks like it could come falling down any\n"
"minute. I can't take my eyes off of it."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Moon01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Tonight's moon will be a little smaller\n"
"than yesterday's full moon. It's nice in\n"
"its own way, really..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
msgctxt "Moon02"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Tonight is the third-quarter moon.<2.pa>\n"
"Like a bow aiming for the heavens above."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "Moon03"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Tonight is the 26th-day moon...<2.pa>\n"
"Its sloping line is really wonderful."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "Moon04"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Tonight is a new moon...<2.pa>\n"
"Even though we can't see it, isn't it\n"
"great just knowing it's there?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
msgctxt "Moon05"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Tonight is a crescent moon...<2.pa>\n"
"That shape makes me hungry for some\n"
"reason..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Moon06"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Tonight is a seven-day moon...\n"
"Like a bow aiming for the land below,\n"
"it really is quite beautiful."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "Moon07"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Tonight is the 13th-day moon...<2.pa>\n"
"Now it will slowly expand. So beautiful..."
msgstr ""

